description:
What is Highcharts?
Highcharts is a charting library written in pure JavaScript, offering an easy way of adding interactive charts to your web site or web application. Highcharts currently supports line, spline, area, areaspline, column, bar, pie and scatter chart types.
Why DotNet Highcharts:
Easy integration with ASP.NET applications.
The output code is pure JavaScript but you need only to write in C#.
Its uses enums and standard classes like Color and DataTime which are converted to JavaScript.
The library is based on classes therefore itâ€™s easy for you to write and format the code.
summary: If you want more interactive and intuitive charts instead of the static chart images, this is the .NET way to display Highcharts into your ASP.NET application.
title: DotNet.Highcharts offers Highcharts integration with ASP.NET applications.
